drug.toxicity:
Oral, rabbit: LD50 = 3200 mg/kg;
Oral, mouse: LD50 = 300 mg/kg;
Oral, rat: LD50: 980 mg/kg;
The most common reasons for discontinuation due to adverse events were dizziness, nausea, vomiting, somnolence, and headache.

drug.absorption:
Bioavailability, immediate release (IR), 86 mg: 32%; 
Bioavailability, extended release (ER), 86 mg: 32%; 
Cmax, IR: 64.2 ng/mL;
Cmax, ER: 22.5 ng/mL; 
T max, IR: 1.5 hours;
T max, ER: 5.0 hours;
Tapentadol accumulates following multiple repeat doses.
